<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FF7D28C0F5FBFDA5" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFBFFC0FF7D28C0F5FBFDA5" blockId="12.[151,760,2014,2070]" lastBlockId="12.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FF7D28C0F01DF826" bold="true" box="[151,268,2014,2038]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe not reaching posterior mar- gin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FC282FC0F507FF25" box="[962,1046,222,245]" captionStart="Figs 2" captionStartId="3.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[235,1334,206,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys bergrothi sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys breddini sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys caquetensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177531/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth, third and less than half of second rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FC022E00F528FEE5" box="[1000,1081,286,309]" captionStart="Figs 9" captionStartId="11.[828,865,2036,2055]" captionText="Figs 9A–B. Hypoxys bergrothi sp. nov.A – genital plates; B – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FBA12E03F419FEE5" bold="true" box="[1099,1288,285,309]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FCAE2E20F289FE85" box="[836,920,318,341]" captionStart="Figs 9" captionStartId="11.[828,865,2036,2055]" captionText="Figs 9A–B. Hypoxys bergrothi sp. nov.A – genital plates; B – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin with posterolateral angles blunt, inner angles short, rounded and directed to valvifers 9; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angle almost reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; inner margin not projected posteriorly; excavation U-shaped. Valvulae 8 visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 clearly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices clearly below imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII. 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FC272D43F562FDA5" bold="true" box="[973,1139,605,629]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FCB02D60F543FC85" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="description">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFBFFC0FCB02D60F543FC85" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FCB02D60F2EAFD45" bold="true" box="[858,1019,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 2; 
<typeStatus id="6C50885EFFFBFFC0FBA32D60F5B7FD45" box="[1097,1190,638,661]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">holotype</typeStatus>
first; mm). Total length 17.2 / 18.3; head length 1.7 /2.0; head width 3.5 / 3.5 (no span); pronotum width 10.3 / 11.5; abdomen width 8.7 / 10.0; length of antennomeres: I – 0.9 / 1.0; II – 1.6 / 1.6; III – 1.5 / 1.5 (no span); IV – 4.2 / 4.4; V – missing; scutellum length 7.9 / 7.9 (no span); scutellum width 5.7 / 6.5; pronotum length 3.4 / 3.5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FCD62C43F59EFC25" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFBFFC0FCD62C43F59EFC25" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FCD62C43F525FCA5" bold="true" box="[828,1076,861,885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFBFFC0FBD12C40F410FCA5" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1083,1281,862,885]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergrothi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FBD12C40F410FCA5" box="[1083,1281,862,885]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Hypoxys bergrothi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFFBFFC0FAE32C40F44DFCA5" box="[1289,1372,862,885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only species that presents valvifers 8 overlapping lateral margin of valvifers 9, leaving the excavation narrow, as narrow as segment X. The other species all have the excavation wider than segment X.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FCD62CE0F419FB85" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFBFFC0FCD62CE0F419FB85" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FCD62CE0F2ACFBC6" bold="true" box="[828,957,1022,1046]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Ernst Evald Bergroth (1857– 1925), the Finnish entomologist that made significant contributions to the study of 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFBFFC0FB852B20F415FB85" authorityName="W.E.Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1135,1284,1086,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pentatomidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
